<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
  xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  dir="ltr"
  metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
  i18n:domain="launchpad"
>

<body>

<metal:leftportlets fill-slot="portlets_one">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-subscribers" />
</metal:leftportlets>

<metal:rightportlets fill-slot="portlets_two">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-details" />
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-bugs" />
</metal:rightportlets>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

      <div>
        <img alt="" src="/@@/question" />
        <a tal:attributes="href context/fmt:url" tal:content="context/title" />
      </div>

  <h1 tal:condition="not: view/subscription">Subscribe to question</h1>
  <h1 tal:condition="view/subscription">Unsubscribe from question</h1>


  <p>
    Subscribing to a question makes it show up on
    <a tal:attributes="href string:/~${request/lp:person/name}/+questions"
    >your Answers page</a>.
  </p>

  <form action="."
        tal:attributes="action request/URL"
        method="post">

    <div class="actions">
      <input tal:condition="not: view/subscription"
             type="submit"
             name="subscribe"
             value="Subscribe" />
      <input tal:condition="view/subscription"
             type="submit"
             name="subscribe"
             value="Unsubscribe" />
    </div>
  </form>

</div>

<metal:help fill-slot="help">
  <p>You can subscribe yourself to this question. When subscribed, you'll
    receive by email all future messages added to the question.
  </p>
  <p>You can use the <emph>Subscribed</emph> report in the <emph>Answers</emph>
    facet of your profile to see all the questions to which you are subscribed.
  </p>
  <p>If you are already subscribed to the question, you can unsubscribe
    yourself from this page.
  </p>
</metal:help>
</body>
</html>
